'Samozaryadnyj Karabin sistemy Simonova'
The SKS is a heavy duty Soviet semi-automatic rifle chambered for the 7.62x39mm round.  This one has been adapted to use detachable magazines and comes with a 20rnd and 30rnd steel magazine.  It also has a muzzle brake and flash suppressor bedded and pined.  The upper wood hand guard was replaced with a steel vented guard for additional cooling of the gas system. It is in great condition and I hate to part with it.

postcontent: I have a pre series 70 Colt model 1911 (mfg in 1918).  It is in excellent shape.  Everything but the barrel is original.  I am looking or a cash offer or a trade for an AR15,  Desert Eagle, or any old cowboy guns  I had some interest by collectors and had the gun checked out and that's when I realized it didn not have the orginal barrel.  The original barrels on these (pre 1920) were all blued.  The barrel in mine is still early (pre series 70) but it is milled.  That does bring the collectible value down a bit, but doesn't kill it by any means.  I will take a reasonable cash offer or trade. This 1911 is close to 100 years old and in outstanding condition and the pre series 70's as we all know are hard to find anymore....especially in good shape.  I just don't shoot it anymore and my interests have changed from the older military weapons to the newer fancier ones.  I always will love the old western stuff..guess thats the kid in me coming out.  It's been in my safe for years, no rusting pitting, not even being fired, just cleaned twice a year. Details:
Looking to sell or trade my Springfield Armory XDm.  This is the 4.5" barreled model chambered in 9x19 parabellum/9mm Luger.  I bought this gun roughly a year ago for personal protection and plinking.  I have put about 500 rounds through the gun and have taken meticulous care of it.  About two months ago I began purchasing a few upgrades for the gun with the hopes of entering some local shooting competitions.  Currently installed on the gun is a FULL Springer Precision Trigger Kit (new trigger bar, sear, springs).  This kit allows for a 50% reduction in trigger travel and a 25% reduction in trigger pull weight.  Also recently installed are Dawson Precision sights.  The rear is fully adjustable for windage and elevation and is serrated black.  The front is matching height fiber optic (comes with red installed, green can be installed and is included).  Excellent sights and trigger allow for rapid, accurate shooting.  The last upgrade is a Springer Precision weighted guide rod.  The added weight in the front of the gun allows for less recoil and faster followup shots.  Also included with the gun is the full set of XDGear and the hard case.  This set includes a paddle holster, dual magazine holster (not pictured but included), speed loader, coil lock, cleaning swab, 2 (19) round magazines, and manual.  Also included are ALL stock parts so the gun can be converted back to normal if desired.  I am listing this firearm at a loss and would much prefer to trade if the right trade comes along.  Additional pictures can be taken upon request.

title: For Sale:  Persian Cossack Saber
postcontent:
Okay, definately picked up some stuff that's not my cup of tea but should interest some collectors!

In the late 19th century Persia/Iran was conflicted ground between several nations and Russia being amongst them. The Russians trained several units of Persian Cossack Calvery which in turn was lead by Russian officers. The Persian 1881 saber is a direct replica of the Russian saber in service at that time.

The one i picked up: All number matching, on scabboard, blade, and hilt. Dints and some rusts on the scabboard but i'll leave it to the collectors to clean it off. The blade has NOT been sharpened which is interesting, perhaps this was never used?

I have no idea on the value of these weapons but i figuered a 19th century legitimate Cossack saber that's all matching and in working condition should be a collector's item

title: For Sale:  Kel-tec PLR22
postcontent:
The PLR-22 pistol is chambered for the popular and economical .22 Long Rifle cartridge (.22LR). It is based on the 5.56mm NATO chambered PLR-16 pistol and shares many parts including the grip and front and rear sights. The PLR-22 is not a simple conversion kit, it is a standalone firearm chambered for the .22LR and is designed for target shooting, plinking, or small game hunting.

The PLR-22 operates by blowback action and has a 4140 steel bolt that rides on steel guide rails inside the polymer receiver. The ejector is attached to one of the guide rails and the recoil spring is located above the barrel. The cross-bolt safety and magazine release operate identically to the PLR-16.

The PLR-22 will accept many of the same accessories as the PLR-16 including the slings, stocks, and compact forend. The rear sight is adjustable for windage and the front sight is adjustable for elevation. An integrated picatinny rail on top will accept a multitude of sighting options. The muzzle end of the barrel is threaded ½”-28 to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake. A 26 round semi-transparent magazine is included and it will accept magazines designed for the Atchison M-16 conversion.



This gun was only removed from the box to take this picture, it is still new in the box and has never been loaded or fired.
